  "why": "The paper does not demonstrate or evaluate transferability of fault-inducing inputs across independently trained models. While the authors apply their LipFuzzer and the same LAPSUS (linguistic) models to both Amazon Alexa and Google Assistant stores, they run fuzzing and verification per-platform and do not present any experiment where inputs (fault-inducing LAPSUS) discovered on one model or platform are reused against a different, unseen target model to measure cross-model transfer. The design also does not include explicit surrogate-model-guided mutation or other mechanisms intended to discover transferable failures across models.",
